OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FScouts accept              
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fresponsibility for teen's  
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Ffall death                 
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Scout leaders have told an inquest they
OL,6, accept responsibility for the death of 
OL,7, a teenager who fell during a hike.     
OL,9,FBen Leonard, 16, from Stockport,       
OL,10,FGreater Manchester, slipped 200ft (61m)
OL,11,Ffrom the Great Orme in Llandudno,      
OL,12,FConwy, on an Explorer Scouts trip in   
OL,13,FAugust 2018.                           
OL,15,FLawyers for the Scout Association told 
OL,16,Fan inquest in Manchester they accepted 
OL,17,Fthey were at fault.                    
OL,19,FJames Ageros KC apologised to Ben's    
OL,20,Fmother, Jackie Leonard, for his death. 
